text.tspan: Self-reported life satisfaction vs. GDP per capita, 2011 to 2024

Self-reported life satisfaction is measured on a
scale
ranging from 0-10, where 10 is the highest possible life
satisfaction. GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and differences in living costs between countries.
Data source: Wellbeing Research Centre (2025); Eurostat, OECD, and World Bank (2025)

Note: GDP per capita is expressed in
international-$
at 2021 prices.
